ners highlights the challenges that have led or will lead to the disappearance of these trees from forests. In doing so, he shows us how diversity loss often disrupts intricately balanced ecosystems and how vital it is that we pay more attention to massive changes in forest composition.With practical steps for the conservation of native tree species, Tree by Tree offers the inspiration and insights we need to begin saving our forests.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aForest declineszNortheastern States. 0aTreesxConservationzNortheastern States. 0aTreesxEcologyzNortheastern States. 4aEnvironmental History. 4aNature Guides & Natural History. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Botany.2bisacsh  aforest dynamics, forest insect pests, tree species loss, forest pathogens, tree extinctions, street trees, nonnative plant invaders, old-growth forest.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501771279?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501771279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501771279/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-123611-7  UIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook 